<paragraph blockId="6.[164,779,1484,1903]" lastBlockId="6.[826,1441,825,1000]" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">
Large species (
<quantity box="[372,473,1514,1535]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.34" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" unit="mm" value="13.4">13.4 mm</quantity>
, 
<typeStatus box="[504,602,1514,1536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">holotype</typeStatus>
) with broad abdomen; males can be separated from all other species by the shape of the superior lobes of genitalia, which are long and stick-like (
<figureCitation box="[539,619,1605,1627]" captionStart="Figures 15–16" captionStartId="6.[164,254,725,744]" captionTargetBox="[419,1188,195,695]" captionTargetId="figure-441@6.[419,1188,195,695]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 15–16. Quichuana argentea sp. nov. male holotype genitalia, lateral view: 15, hypandrium; 16, epandrium. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5408543" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5408543/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
), and by the shape and size of surstyli (
<figureCitation box="[469,549,1636,1658]" captionStart="Figures 15–16" captionStartId="6.[164,254,725,744]" captionTargetBox="[419,1188,195,695]" captionTargetId="figure-441@6.[419,1188,195,695]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 15–16. Quichuana argentea sp. nov. male holotype genitalia, lateral view: 15, hypandrium; 16, epandrium. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5408543" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5408543/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); without an examination of genitalia, males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray, 2012" authorityName="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray" authorityYear="2012" box="[507,637,1667,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[507,637,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">Q. argentea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[644,729,1667,1688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be separated from males of the similar 
<taxonomicName authority="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray, 2012" authorityName="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salvadorensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">Q. salvadorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[227,311,1728,1749]" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the pale colour of the body hairs, which are white in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray, 2012" authorityName="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray" authorityYear="2012" box="[411,542,1759,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[411,542,1759,1780]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">Q. argentea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[549,634,1759,1780]" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and golden yellow in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray, 2012" authorityName="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray" authorityYear="2012" box="[283,470,1789,1810]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salvadorensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[283,470,1789,1810]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">Q. salvadorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[477,564,1789,1810]" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray, 2012" authorityName="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">Q. argentea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[244,328,1820,1841]" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from females of the similar 
<taxonomicName authority="Hull, 1951" authorityName="Hull CNC" authorityYear="1951" box="[310,687,1850,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hermosa">
<emphasis box="[310,546,1850,1871]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">Quichuana hermosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hull FM" box="[560,687,1850,1872]" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" pagination="65 - 70" refId="ref46566" refString="Hull FM. 1951. Some new species of syrphid flies. Journal of the New York Entomological Society 54: 65 - 70." type="journal article" year="1951">Hull, 1951</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the length of the pollinose stripes on the scutum, which end halfway between the TS and the posterior margin of the scutum in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray, 2012" authorityName="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray" authorityYear="2012" box="[1068,1199,856,878]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1068,1199,856,878]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">Q. argentea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1206,1290,857,878]" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and reach, although faintly, the posterior margin of the scutum in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hull CNC" authorityYear="1951" box="[861,989,917,939]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hermosa">
<emphasis box="[861,989,917,939]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">Q. hermosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; fore- and mesofemur are extensively red in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray, 2012" authorityName="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray" authorityYear="2012" box="[903,1034,948,970]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[903,1034,948,970]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">Q. argentea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1041,1128,948,969]" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, whereas they are only red apically in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hull CNC" authorityYear="1951" box="[958,1086,978,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hermosa">
<emphasis box="[958,1086,978,1000]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">Q. hermosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
